The Inter-Party Advisory Council (IPAC) in Benue State, has urged stakeholders in Saturday’s runoff elections to strictly abide by the rules of the game. Chairman of IPAC in the state, Godwin Odeh, in a statement made available to newsmen in Makurdi used the opportunity to express appreciation to the electorate in the state for their untiring efforts to elect their leaders. He however called on Benue people to come out in their numbers on Saturday and exercise their civic responsibility. “We the leadership of the Inter-Party Advisory Council (IPAC) in Benue State wish to express appreciation to the electorate in the state for turning out to exercise their civic responsibility at the last elections in a peaceful manner. “We call on the people of the state to come out in their numbers on Saturday, March 23, to conclude that they had started on the 9th of the same month,” Odeh stated. IPAC appeals to candidates, parties to accept defeat Anambra guber: Voters eagerly await epic polls FCT IPAC inaugurates new executives